data.title: Stressed Out (Twenty One Pilots)
data.meta_description: Stressed Out is a song written and recorded by American alternative hip hop band Twenty One Pilots for their fourth studio album, Blurryface (2015).…

I WISH= always followed by a past tense:

- I wish I had a pet elephant

- I wish you were here

This is actually an "unreal past" tense (or subjunctive), so for the verb "to be" we have to use "were" for all persons:

- I wish I were rich

But in modern English (esp. AmE.) it is now common to use it as a normal past tense and say:

- I wish I was rich

CHORDS= /kɔ:*d/ Harmony. A musical combination of different notes.

SANG= We were now expecting a word rhyming with NEW, but there is no rhyme, so he made his wish come true: I wish I didn't have to rhyme every time I sang.

I WAS TOLD= They told me (especial passive used when the agent or doer of the action is "some people", unidentified)

SHRINK= Become smaller.

BLURRYFACE= The album is named after a character the band created called Blurryface. According to Joseph, he "represents all the things that I as an individual, but also everyone around, are insecure about." Joseph wears black paint on his hands and neck during his live shows and music videos for the album, to represent Blurryface, saying: "Very dramatic, I know, but it helps me get into that character."

WISH = (I) wish.

TURN BACK TIME= Go back to the past.

OL'= (informal) Old.

MOMMA= AmE spelling /mɑmɑ/ mum, mother.

SANG US TO SLPEEP= If your mum sings you to sleep, she sings a song for you to help you sleep (for example, a lullaby to babies)

STRESSED OUT= (informal) stressed, anxious, tense.

HOW COME?= (informal) Why?

I'M NEVER ABLE TO= I can never.

I'D MAKE A CANDLE OUT OF IT= I'd make a candle with that stuff (made using the smell as material)

SELL OUT= Sell it cheap (because I want to sell all of it).

'CAUSE= (informal) Because.

HOMEGROWN= characteristic of a place; local; originated at home.

CREEK= A small stream (a little river)

ROAM= To move around a place with no destiny or purpose.

STUDENT LOANS= Money the bank lends you to pay for your studies and then, when you get a job, you must pay back.

TREEHOUSE= A wooden house on top of a tree (usually built for playing around)

USED TO= If you used to do something, you did that often in the past as a habit, but not now anymore (a past habit which doesn't exist in the present)

TO PLAY PRETEND= A game in which you pretend to be someone different (for example you pretend to be superman).

WOULD= Used to (see above)

A ROCKET SHIP= A spaceship which is a rocket (see picture)

OUTER SPACE= Space outside our planet's atmosphere.

BUNNY= (noun) silly.
